<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_2e13ebd0-b670-4875-bc73-a00e555d9e75" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>I2D2</sptc><title id="_a575e610-5d6c-4cab-aae3-ea68efc5a896">Accessways</title><archive-num>2019: H2.2</archive-num><subclause id="_f3327405-6712-4c32-a5b9-707330fcc728" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_fdf44bae-0d2b-45fc-9ea4-678c533eabd8">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>An <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1174_1.1.0.xml#_a9dd8ca7-e567-403a-bff7-e567012e1849" id="_f37ad1ec-a0dd-489a-beab-78282d60b366" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">accessway</xref> must comply with AS 1428.2.</p></subclause><subclause id="_42875112-d34e-4cd2-a3d9-3e3cfcac4937" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_ce9eb189-f42e-4948-aa96-ac66e9024662">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>If an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1174_1.1.0.xml#_a9dd8ca7-e567-403a-bff7-e567012e1849" id="_63d0c787-b841-4253-be29-8fff4e44cadf" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">accessway</xref> branches into 2 or more parallel tracks—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_345f9927-5bf3-4f12-b19e-e3eb3351e3c9">the ends of each track must be on the main pedestrian traffic routes; and</li><li id="_5ae77923-4e6c-429a-b60d-4ae564a1e017">the parallel tracks must have equal convenience and be located as close as practicable to the main pedestrian branch.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_c7bdf214-0183-413d-a48b-655f28365a98" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_3846a66d-dfa3-437d-ad9b-64495ca04b56">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>The minimum unobstructed width of an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1174_1.1.0.xml#_a9dd8ca7-e567-403a-bff7-e567012e1849" id="_b113676c-4f75-4821-8fd8-d9aeb0497220" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">accessway</xref> must be 1.2 m, except that—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_d73321c8-9838-492d-914f-06c05dd69d75">the minimum unobstructed width of a moving walkway forming part of an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1174_1.1.0.xml#_a9dd8ca7-e567-403a-bff7-e567012e1849" id="_403d8561-458a-42e3-b723-0f0b35def909" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">accessway</xref> may be not less than 850 mm; and</li><li id="_d3a71035-4a73-47ca-afe8-30e2b5e6ae6e">the minimum unobstructed width of a doorway in an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1174_1.1.0.xml#_a9dd8ca7-e567-403a-bff7-e567012e1849" id="_db30e2bb-b6e6-4033-9aea-9194cfdcee40" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">accessway</xref> may be not less than 850 mm.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_4a9f76d8-c51a-4d68-8789-9a6fc7d12f11" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_2255a5d4-538e-4a95-9b75-e579e212cbd7">SubClause</title><num>4</num><p>Poles, columns, stanchions, bollards and fixtures must not project into an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1174_1.1.0.xml#_a9dd8ca7-e567-403a-bff7-e567012e1849" id="_f88d6308-a45d-4328-9845-42948c216fa8" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">accessway</xref>.</p></subclause><subclause id="_6b668291-823a-4c2b-8ef1-656f3400c7e7" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_b2a5d3c4-df9d-438e-bb8b-63d8ca5fe456">SubClause</title><num>5</num><p>Obstacles that abut an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1174_1.1.0.xml#_a9dd8ca7-e567-403a-bff7-e567012e1849" id="_6d709fe2-fb2a-4ef2-9536-278ab6fa501c" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">accessway</xref> must have a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1368_0.4.0.xml#_a01e03e9-1ea5-4a56-980c-85d53fd9cb5b" id="_dd8573eb-1ba4-456a-8143-f7ee52dbb0cd" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">luminance contrast</xref> with a background of not less than 30%.</p></subclause><subclause id="_b0d9a17b-b802-4751-9c1a-6d2b9f61d789" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_ea7641c2-3e77-4b1a-a1f4-9e3dee6ab706">SubClause</title><num>6</num><p>Manoeuvring areas that allow a 180 degree wheelchair turn must comply with clause 6.2 of AS 1428.2.</p></subclause><subclause id="_fb479720-2cb5-45f3-952c-e0bad6bbff23" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_1bd17912-8752-4b23-a178-173de2118b3e">SubClause</title><num>7</num><p>A passing area must be provided at least every 6 m along any two-way <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1174_1.1.0.xml#_a9dd8ca7-e567-403a-bff7-e567012e1849" id="_c77ba830-882b-401e-8e01-98f8ca37371a" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">accessway</xref> that is less than 1800 mm wide.</p></subclause><subclause id="_b515fdcf-4f73-4586-afb6-15afec09d9c1" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_73ec843c-018d-4fc5-af2d-a0697b0ff459">SubClause</title><num>8</num><p>Ground and floor surfaces must comply with clause 9 of AS 1428.2 and AS 1428.1 Supplement 1 provides criteria for the selection of floor surfaces.</p></subclause><subclause id="_4c18607c-5c2e-4b16-9f54-a33b84337dbc" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_c7ce3bff-7136-4898-9db5-1765e25e7e82">SubClause</title><num>9</num><p>The requirements of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/2047_1.3.0.xml#_65ebcb8d-f8c8-4d6f-9c51-983181aa4992" id="_4bf20878-9270-4d08-9d35-7d5485f93a8b" scope="local" type="clause">D4D4(c)(ii)</xref> do not apply to Class 9b or Class 10 public transport buildings.</p></subclause></clause>